Package: pi-gen-micro
Architecture: arm64
Pre-Depends: dpkg (>= 1.16.1)
Depends: rpi-make-boot-image, sed (>= 4.9), libc6 (>= 2.36), bash (>= 5.2)
Description: Tool to create cut-down Debian-based OS-images for Raspberry Pi Devices
 pi-gen-micro is a lightweight tool for creating minimal Debian-based
 operating system images optimized for Raspberry Pi devices. It allows
 for customization of the base system while maintaining a small footprint,
 making it ideal for embedded systems and IoT applications that require
 a compact, efficient OS with the reliability of Debian, and the enhanced
 features of Raspberry Pi OS.
 .
 This package includes utilities and scripts necessary for building
 custom Raspberry Pi OS images with reduced size and resource requirements.
